const faqs = [
  { q: 'Are all 392 calculators completely free?', a: 'Yes — every single calculator on tooltrio.com is 100% free, permanently. There are no premium tiers, no subscription plans, no hidden fees, and no feature locks. We believe professional-grade calculation tools should be accessible to every American regardless of income. Open any tool and use it as many times as you want, forever.' },
  { q: 'Do I need to create an account to use these tools?', a: 'No account required — ever. You can use all 392 calculators without providing an email address, phone number, or any personal information. Just open the tool and start calculating. There is no registration wall, no email verification, and no "free trial" that expires. Every tool works immediately for everyone.' },
  { q: 'Is my personal data stored or shared?', a: 'No. All calculations run entirely within your browser using client-side JavaScript. Nothing you enter — health data, financial figures, income, passwords, code — is ever transmitted to any server, stored in any database, or shared with any third party. When you close the browser tab, all your inputs disappear permanently. We have no ability to access your data because it never leaves your device.' },
  { q: 'How accurate are the financial calculators for US users?', a: 'Our finance calculators use current 2026 IRS tax brackets, contribution limits (401k: $23,500, IRA: $7,000, HSA: $4,300 for 2025), and US market conventions. Formulas follow standards from the CFP Board, IRS, SEC, and FINRA. Results are planning estimates — actual investment returns vary with market performance, and tax laws change annually. For major financial decisions, verify current limits at IRS.gov and consult a Certified Financial Planner (CFP).' },
  { q: 'How accurate are the health calculators?', a: 'Health calculators use validated formulas from the CDC, NIH, AHA, WHO, and Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics. The BMI calculator uses CDC standard categories, calorie calculators use the Mifflin-St Jeor equation (most accurate for American adults per peer-reviewed research), and heart risk calculators use Framingham risk score methodology. Results are population-level estimates — individual results may vary based on genetics, medications, and medical conditions. Always discuss health changes with your physician.' },
  { q: 'Do these calculators work for UK and European users?', a: 'Yes. We have 30+ dedicated UK calculators covering 2025/26 PAYE income tax, National Insurance, ISA allowances (Stocks & Shares, Cash, Lifetime), stamp duty (SDLT), UK pension auto-enrolment, SIPP vs. ISA comparison, and more. European tools cover VAT for all EU member states, European mortgage rates, MSCI World vs. S&P 500 comparison, and FIRE planning at European safe withdrawal rates. All calculators support GBP, EUR, and USD.' },
  { q: 'Do these tools work on iPhones, Android, and tablets?', a: 'Yes — all 392 calculators are fully responsive and work on every device. Tested on iPhone (iOS 16+), Android (Chrome, Samsung Internet), iPad, Mac (Safari, Chrome), and Windows PC (Chrome, Edge, Firefox). No app download required. Simply open any calculator in your mobile browser and it works perfectly. The interface automatically optimizes for your screen size.' },
  { q: 'How often are the calculators updated?', a: 'Finance calculators are updated annually to reflect new IRS contribution limits, tax bracket adjustments, and regulatory changes. Health calculators are updated when major US health organizations revise their guidelines (CDC, NIH, AHA updates are monitored continuously). Developer tools are updated when standards bodies release new specifications. The last site-wide update was for the 2026 tax year.' },
  { q: 'Can I use these calculators for professional or commercial purposes?', a: 'Yes. Financial advisors, registered dietitians, software developers, educators, and other professionals use our calculators as reference tools and for client education. Results can be shared with clients, included in reports, and used in professional practice. No commercial license or attribution is required. For regulated financial or medical advice, always apply your professional judgment alongside our calculations.' },
  { q: 'What makes tooltrio.com different from other calculator sites?', a: 'Three things: depth, privacy, and US-focus. With 392 calculators across finance, health, developer tools, and fun categories, we offer the broadest free calculator library available to Americans. Every tool is privacy-first (zero data transmission, zero storage). And every finance calculator is built specifically for the US market — using American units, IRS tax laws, and US market benchmarks by default, unlike generic international calculators that require manual adjustment.' },
]

